refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
arraycubrid_fetch_array resourceresult inttypeCUBRID_BOTH
La función cubrid_fetch_array se utiliza para consultar una única fila del resultado de la consulta, y lo devuelve como array. El cursor avanza automáticamente a la siguiente fila del resultado.

  &reftitle.examples;

   Ejemplo de cubrid_fetch_array


<?php
$conn = cubrid_connect("localhost", 33000, "demodb");
$req = cubrid_execute($conn, "SELECT name,area,seats,address FROM stadium WHERE nation_code='GRE' AND seats > 10000");

printf("%-40s %-10s %-6s %-20s\n", "name", "area", "seats", "address");
while ($row = cubrid_fetch_array($req, CUBRID_NUM)) {
    printf("%-40s %-10s %-6s %-20s\n", $row[0], $row[1], $row[2], $row[3]);
}

cubrid_close_request($req);

cubrid_disconnect($conn);
?>


